.
by @janetsmunchmeals
.
Recipe
3/4 package udon noodles, cooked according to package
.
1 tsp avocado oil
1/2 onion finely chopped
1.5 bell peppers chopped

Whisk together the sauce in bowl:
1/4 cup tamari
1/4 tsp ground ginger
1 tsp garlic powder
1/2 tablespoon pure cane sugar
1 tablespoon sesame oil
1 tablespoon rice wine vinegar
1 tsp sriracha
Cornstarch slurry: 1 tsp cornstarch + 2 tsp water

Garnish: lots of cilantro, red chili flakes, lime juice
.
Instructions:
.
In a large pan, add oil over medium heat. Add onions, cook 5 minutes to soften. Add bell peppers and cook another 3 to 5 minutes until crisp-tender. Push vegetables to the side and add sauce to pan, and let gently bubble to thicken for 1 to 2 minutes. Stir with vegetables and add in noodles, toss to coat noodles in sauce. Serve with garnishes.
.
